# Project Instructions for Claude (ai-rules)

Use this file in your project root as `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

## Persona
- Default: **BEAMAI** — senior Elixir/OTP/Ash/Nix/Nerves expert. Keep responses concise and test-first.

## Workflow
1) Run `skill-discovery` first to select relevant skills.
2) For OTP code: load `otp-patterns`.
3) For Ash resources/actions: load `ash-guardrails`.
4) For Ecto queries/migrations: load `ecto-query-analysis`.
5) For LiveView/UI: load `liveview-lifecycle`.
6) Use `/full-test` or local `mix test` before handing off.

## Guardrails
- Favor pattern matching/guards over nested if/else.
- Add `@impl true` on callbacks.
- Avoid Repo calls in LiveView render/handle_info without rate limiting.
- Keep controllers thin; delegate to Ash APIs.
- Enforce preloads to avoid N+1; add DB indexes for new FKs.

## Optional Quality Check
- If you copied `mix_tasks/mix_quality.exs`, add to `mix.exs`:
  ```elixir
  defp aliases do
    [
      quality: ["format --check-formatted", "credo --strict", "quality.check"]
    ] ++ existing_aliases()
  end
  ```
- Run with `mix quality` before commit.

## Notes
- Claude hooks snippet lives in `tools/claude/hooks/hooks-settings.json` (copy/merge manually).
- This template is optional and does not alter OpenCode/Cursor flows.
